The county should rehabilitate run-down markets before the rains begin so traders and customers do not have difficulty accessing them, Kiambu Senator Kimani Wamatangi said yesterday.He said businesses suffer when the area is muddy because clients avoid it. Some markets do not have roofs and concrete floors, Wamatangi said in Limuru.He said all markets in Limuru and some in other areas do not have roofs. Roofs in markets are very important since they also protect some commodities such as cereals, Wamatangi said.Human rights activist Pacifica Ongecha said toilets in the markets should be upgraded to avoid spread of diseases.